      "content": "1. The \"Noble Savage\" stereotype, portraying people of color as inherently noble, pure, or primitive.\n2. The \"Jungle Island\" trope, depicting non-white characters as living in exotic, undeveloped, or dangerous places.\n3. The \"Sassy Black Woman,\" who is often portrayed as loud, aggressive, or overly sexualized.\n4. The \"Model Minority,\" which falsely homogenizes people of color as hardworking, successful, and without issues.\n5. The \"Magical Negro,\" a character who exists solely to help the white protagonist, often with supernatural abilities or wisdom.\n\nIt's important to avoid these stereotypes and instead aim for authentic, multi-dimensional characters that reflect the diversity of real people. Subverting these tropes can be done thoughtfully and respectfully, contributing to a more inclusive and accurate representation in media.",
